node.text:
The untamed beauty of the outdoors through the lens of Austrian photographer @josefwittibschlager 🏔️✨ #MadeWithLightroom

"I’m Josef Wittibschlager, a mountain and outdoor photographer based in Amstetten, Austria. For me, there has never been anything better than capturing unique moments with a camera and publishing these unique outdoor experiences in the form of pictures. The peace and creativity that outdoor photography offers are an ideal retreat.

For my post-production, I use Adobe Lightroom. I really like images with deep blacks and strong whites, so I prefer to deepen my shadows and brighten the lights a bit. I almost always create a version of the classic ‘S’ curve. The 'S' curve deepens the shadows and brightens the lighter parts. It helps shape the atmosphere and mood of my photos."
@lightroom yes! All my picture are edited by Lightroom 🔥
@anaradolovic When it's cold but you feel the heat 🔥
Those blue tones always look amazing! 🙌 Stunning and marvelous photos!👏
@zeyamedya ALL the feels on this masterpiece 🥶
@josefwittibschlager Light like this doesn’t just happen, it's earned. Incredible work. 👏
